Dear Luc Valette-EIS,

I already configured  check_udp_flood command, template and service in Juniper Host.

This is the command:
/usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_snmp -C $_SERVICECOMMUNITY$  -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -o NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsAttkMonUdpFlood.1 --rate -w $_SERVICEWARNING$  -c $_SERVICECRITICAL$

NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsAttkMonUdpFlood.1  is a counter that update when achieve thresold of
NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsUdpFloodThresh.1 = INTEGER: 10000


For multi-auth-fail  I found a OID NETSCREEN-INTERFACE-MIB::nsIfMonAuthFail  a counter if auth fail.
For test this OID is working properly. Could you provide me:

- Smtp server ( domain name )  and port  ?

For large imcp I found an OID  NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsDetectIcmpLarge.1

- To work with this functionality Juniper should be enable, actually is disable
    (NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsDetectIcmpFrag.1  ==  disable )
     Could you activate?

Kipitapp service team.

Alberto Galan



PROTECTZONEID=$(/usr/lib/plugins/protectzoneid.sh $_ZONENAME$ $HOSTADDRESS$ $_SERVICECOMMUNITY$) &&  /usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_snmp -C $_SERVICECOMMUNITY$  -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -o NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsAttkMonUdpFlood.$PROTECTZONEID --rate -w $_SERVICEWARNING$ -c $_SERVICECRITICAL$

/usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_snmp -C community  -H 192.168.7.2 -o NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsAttkMonUdpFlood.$PROTECTZONEID --rate -w 2 -c 2



/usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_snmp -C $_SERVICECOMMUNITY$  -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -o NETSCREEN-IDS-MIB::nsIdsAttkMonUdpFlood.1 --rate -w $_SERVICEWARNING$ -c $_SERVICECRITICAL$

/usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_centreon_snmp_traffic -v 2 --64-bits -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -C $_SERVICECOMMUNITY$ -i $_SERVICEINTERFACE$ -w $_SERVICEWARNING$ -c $_SERVICECRITICAL$


